%20waste-related%20impacts%20using%20the%20following%20criteria:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Quantity%20of%20inputs%20used%20to%20produce%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20products%20or%20services,%20which%20will%20become%20waste%20after%20they%20are%20used%20for%20production.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Quantity%20of%20waste%20outputs%20generated%20in%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20own%20activities,%20or%20quantity%20of%20outputs%20it%20provides%20to%20entities%20downstream%20that%20will%20eventually%20become%20waste%20when%20they%20reach%20their%20end%20of%20life.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Hazardous%20characteristics%20of%20inputs%20and%20outputs.%20&bull;%20Properties%20of%20input%20materials%20or%20design%20characteristics%20of%20outputs%20that%20limit%20or%20prevent%20their%20recovery%20or%20limit%20the%20length%20of%20their%20life.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Known%20potential%20negative%20threats%20associated%20with%20specific%20materials%20when%20they%20are%20discarded.%20For%20example,%20the%20potential%20threat%20of%20marine%20pollution%20resulting%20from%20leakage%20of%20discarded%20plastic%20packaging%20into%20waterbodies.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Types%20of%20activities%20that%20lead%20to%20significant%20quantities%20of%20waste%20generation%20or%20to%20generation%20of%20hazardous%20waste.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20report%20on%20inputs%20that%20it%20receives%20from%20entities%20upstream%20in%20its%20value%20chain,%20as%20well%20as%20outputs%20it%20provides%20to%20entities%20downstream%20in%20its%20value%20chain.%20For%20example,%20if%20an%20organization%20procures%20components%20with%20hazardous%20characteristics%20from%20a%20supplier%20and%20uses%20these%20in%20a%20product%20that%20will%20continue%20to%20carry%20these%20components%20and%20their%20hazardous%20characteristics,%20the%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20report%20these%20components%20under%20inputs%20that%20lead%20or%20could%20lead%20to%20significant%20waste-related%20impacts.%20Similarly,%20if%20an%20organization%20sells%20to%20consumers%20products%20that%20generate%20large%20quantities%20of%20packaging%20waste,%20it%20is%20required%20to%20report%20this%20packaging%20under%20outputs%20that%20lead%20or%20could%20lead%20to%20significant%20waste-related%20impacts.If%20the%20organization%20has%20identified%20many%20inputs%20and%20outputs%20or%20many%20activities%20that%20lead%20or%20could%20lead%20to%20significant%20waste-related%20impacts,%20it%20may%20group%20these%20by:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20product%20or%20service%20category%20that%20the%20inputs%20and%20outputs%20relate%20to;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20business%20units%20or%20facilities%20that%20procure%20the%20inputs,%20or%20whose%20activities%20produce%20the%20outputs;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20categories%20of%20upstream%20and%20downstream%20activities%20that%20produce%20the%20outputs%20(for%20examples%20of%20upstream%20and%20downstream%20categories,%20see%20the%20guidance%20for%20Disclosure%20302-2%20in%20GRI%20302:%20Energy%202016).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%201.2%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EA%20process%20flow%20is%20a%20tool%20to%20visualize%20the%20information%20required%20to%20be%20reported%20under%20Disclosure%20306-1.%20A%20graphic%20illustration%20of%20the%20process%20flow%20can%20help%20the%20organization%20and%20its%20stakeholders%20understand%20how%20inputs%20and%20outputs%20move%20through%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20own%20activities%20as%20well%20as%20through%20the%20activities%20of%20entities%20upstream%20and%20downstream%20in%20its%20value%20chain.%20It%20shows%20where%20waste%20is%20generated%20in%20the%20value%20chain%20or%20where%20outputs%20become%20waste.%20The%20organization%20can%20also%20use%20the%20process%20flow%20to%20illustrate%20information%20that%20is%20required%20under%20other%20disclosures%20of%20this%20Standard,%20such%20as:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20actions%20taken%20to%20prevent%20waste%20generation%20(Disclosure%20306-2);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20composition%20of%20waste%20generated%20(Disclosure%20306-3);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20recovery%20operations%20used%20to%20divert%20waste%20from%20disposal%20(Disclosure%20306-4);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20disposal%20operations%20(Disclosure%20306-5).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20include%20estimates%20of%20the%20weight%20of%20inputs%20and%20the%20weight%20of%20outputs%20in%20metric%20tons%20or%20the%20ratio%20of%20inputs%20to%20outputs.For%20examples%20of%20process%20flow%20illustrations,%20see%20the%20Appendix.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20306-2%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EAn%20organization%20can%20cause%20waste-related%20impacts%20through%20its%20own%20activities.%20For%20example,%20when%20its%20operations%20generate%20waste%20outputs.%20It%20can%20also%20contribute%20to%20waste-related%20impacts%20through%20activities%20carried%20out%20in%20its%20value%20chain%20upstream%20or%20downstream.%20For%20example,%20through%20criteria%20in%20its%20procurement%20policies%20that%20lead%20to%20waste%20generation%20upstream,%20or%20through%20management%20decisions%20that%20limit%20the%20life%20of%20its%20products%20and%20therefore%20contribute%20to%20waste%20generation%20downstream.%20Even%20when%20the%20organization%20has%20not%20contributed%20to%20waste-related%20impacts%20upstream%20or%20downstream%20in%20its%20value%20chain,%20its%20operations,%20products,%20or%20services%20could%20be%20directly%20linked%20to%20waste-related%20impacts%20by%20its%20business%20relationships%20with%20the%20entities%20in%20its%20value%20chain.%20For%20example,%20when%20third%20parties%20hired%20by%20the%20organization%20carry%20out%20inadequate%20recovery%20or%20di