perations%20and%20the%20aftercare%20of%20disposal%20sites.%20The%20organization%20may%20specify%20agreements%20in%20a%20contract%20for%20the%20third%20party%20to%20follow%20when%20managing%20its%20waste,%20or%20rely%20on%20existing%20legislative%20obligations,%20such%20as%20local%20environmental%20laws%20and%20regulations,%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20third%20party%20manages%20the%20waste%20adequately.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20306-2-c%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20processes%20that%20the%20organization%20has%20in%20place%20for%20collecting%20and%20monitoring%20waste-related%20data%20can%20reflect%20its%20commitment%20to%20managing%20waste-related%20impacts.%20Such%20processes%20can%20include%20online%20data%20entry,&nbsp;maintaining%20a%20centralized%20database,%20real-time%20weighbridge%20measurement,%20and%20annual%20external%20data%20validation.%20The%20organization%20can%20specify%20whether%20the%20data%20collection%20and%20monitoring%20processes%20extend%20beyond%20waste%20generated%20in%20its%20own%20activities%20to%20include%20waste%20generated%20upstream%20and%20downstream%20in%20its%20value%20chain.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20total%20weight%20of%20waste%20generated,%20when%20contrasted%20with%20the%20weight%20of%20waste%20that%20the%20organization%20directs%20to%20recovery%20and%20disposal,%20can%20show%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20the%20organization%20manages%20its%20waste-related%20impacts.The%20composition%20of%20the%20waste%20generated%20can%20help%20identify%20recovery%20or%20disposal%20operations%20appropriate%20to%20the%20type%20of%20waste%20and%20to%20the%20specific%20materials%20present%20in%20the%20waste.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20init